Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.Questionnaire.item` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-Questionnaire.item Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-10 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionQuestionnaire_Item

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element Questionnaire.item for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Extension.extension

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • This Extension is not used by any profiles in this Implementation Guide

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element Questionnaire.item for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: string: An identifier that is unique within the Questionnaire allowing linkage to the equivalent item in a QuestionnaireResponse resource.
  • definition: uri: This element is a URI that refers to an ElementDefinition or to an ObservationDefinition that provides information about this item, including information that might otherwise be included in the instance of the Questionnaire resource. A detailed description of the construction of the URI is shown in Comments, below.
  • code: Coding: A terminology code that corresponds to this group or question (e.g. a code from LOINC, which defines many questions and answers).
  • prefix: string: A short label for a particular group, question or set of display text within the questionnaire used for reference by the individual completing the questionnaire.
  • text: string: The name of a section, the text of a question or text content for a display item.
  • type: code: The type of questionnaire item this is - whether text for display, a grouping of other items or a particular type of data to be captured (string, integer, Coding, etc.).
  • question: string: The linkId for the question whose answer (or lack of answer) governs whether this item is enabled.
  • operator: code: Specifies the criteria by which the question is enabled.
  • answer: boolean, decimal, integer, date, dateTime, time, string, Coding, Quantity, Reference: A value that the referenced question is tested using the specified operator in order for the item to be enabled. If there are multiple answers, a match on any of the answers suffices. If different behavior is desired (all must match, at least 2 must match, etc.), consider using the enableWhenExpression extension.
  • enableBehavior: code: Controls how multiple enableWhen values are interpreted - whether all or any must be true.
  • disabledDisplay: code: Indicates if and how items that are disabled (because enableWhen evaluates to 'false') should be displayed.
  • required: boolean: An indication, if true, that the item must be present in a "completed" QuestionnaireResponse. If false, the item may be skipped when answering the questionnaire.
  • repeats: boolean: An indication, if true, that a QuestionnaireResponse for this item may include multiple answers associated with a single instance of this item (for question-type items) or multiple repetitions of the item (for group-type items).
  • readOnly: boolean: An indication, when true, that the value cannot be changed by a human respondent to the Questionnaire.
  • maxLength: integer: The maximum number of characters that are permitted in the answer to be considered a "valid" QuestionnaireResponse.
  • answerConstraint: code: For items that have a defined set of allowed answers (via answerOption or answerValueSet), indicates whether values other than those specified can be selected.
  • answerValueSet: canonical: A reference to a value set containing a list of values representing permitted answers for a question.
  • value: integer, date, time, string, Coding, Reference: A potential answer that's allowed as the answer to this question.
  • initialSelected: boolean: Indicates whether the answer value is selected when the list of possible answers is initially shown.
  • value: boolean, decimal, integer, date, dateTime, time, string, uri, Attachment, Coding, Quantity, Reference: The actual value to for an initial answer.
  • item: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Text, questions and other groups to be nested beneath a question or group.

Maturity: 0

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element Questionnaire.item for use in FHIR R4.

  • linkId: string: An identifier that is unique within the Questionnaire allowing linkage to the equivalent item in a QuestionnaireResponse resource.
  • definition: uri: This element is a URI that refers to an ElementDefinition or to an ObservationDefinition that provides information about this item, including information that might otherwise be included in the instance of the Questionnaire resource. A detailed description of the construction of the URI is shown in Comments, below.
  • code: Coding: A terminology code that corresponds to this group or question (e.g. a code from LOINC, which defines many questions and answers).
  • prefix: string: A short label for a particular group, question or set of display text within the questionnaire used for reference by the individual completing the questionnaire.
  • text: string: The name of a section, the text of a question or text content for a display item.
  • type: code: The type of questionnaire item this is - whether text for display, a grouping of other items or a particular type of data to be captured (string, integer, Coding, etc.).
  • question: string: The linkId for the question whose answer (or lack of answer) governs whether this item is enabled.
  • operator: code: Specifies the criteria by which the question is enabled.
  • answer: boolean, decimal, integer, date, dateTime, time, string, Coding, Quantity, Reference: A value that the referenced question is tested using the specified operator in order for the item to be enabled. If there are multiple answers, a match on any of the answers suffices. If different behavior is desired (all must match, at least 2 must match, etc.), consider using the enableWhenExpression extension.
  • enableBehavior: code: Controls how multiple enableWhen values are interpreted - whether all or any must be true.
  • disabledDisplay: code: Indicates if and how items that are disabled (because enableWhen evaluates to 'false') should be displayed.
  • required: boolean: An indication, if true, that the item must be present in a "completed" QuestionnaireResponse. If false, the item may be skipped when answering the questionnaire.
  • repeats: boolean: An indication, if true, that a QuestionnaireResponse for this item may include multiple answers associated with a single instance of this item (for question-type items) or multiple repetitions of the item (for group-type items).
  • readOnly: boolean: An indication, when true, that the value cannot be changed by a human respondent to the Questionnaire.
  • maxLength: integer: The maximum number of characters that are permitted in the answer to be considered a "valid" QuestionnaireResponse.
  • answerConstraint: code: For items that have a defined set of allowed answers (via answerOption or answerValueSet), indicates whether values other than those specified can be selected.
  • answerValueSet: canonical: A reference to a value set containing a list of values representing permitted answers for a question.
  • value: integer, date, time, string, Coding, Reference: A potential answer that's allowed as the answer to this question.
  • initialSelected: boolean: Indicates whether the answer value is selected when the list of possible answers is initially shown.
  • value: boolean, decimal, integer, date, dateTime, time, string, uri, Attachment, Coding, Quantity, Reference: The actual value to for an initial answer.
  • item: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Text, questions and other groups to be nested beneath a question or group.

Maturity: 0
